1
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:02,060
Greetings everyone.

2
00:00:02,820 --> 00:00:08,580
Equipped this lazy converter construction with voltage feedback.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:13,140
Now it stably holds 238 V at output.

4
00:00:14,440 --> 00:00:17,720
Feedback also done quite simply.

5
00:00:17,880 --> 00:00:19,800
These are two additional microchips.

6
00:00:20,540 --> 00:00:27,500
One of them optocoupler PC817, other — controllable zener TL431.

7
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:32,240
4 resistances, 1 capacitor.

8
00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:34,380
That's all feedback.

9
00:00:35,040 --> 00:00:43,280
Thus, this converter got possibility to supply at input not only 12 V but also up to 20 V inclusive.

10
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:48,900
In any range of voltages of this order.

11
00:00:49,580 --> 00:00:52,840
And stabilized output voltage.

12
00:00:53,720 --> 00:01:00,940
Now we'll test it and further examine feedback scheme.

13
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:06,320
Now will test trigger point of voltage feedback.

14
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:11,340
To output connected tester, with this lamp not connected.

15
00:01:12,460 --> 00:01:14,560
Apply power 12 V.

16
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:22,320
Visible that converter trigger point by sound audible starts to buzz.

17
00:01:23,920 --> 00:01:26,000
Such sound comes out.

18
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:28,140
237 V.

19
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:32,060
Connect lamp.

20
00:01:32,820 --> 00:01:36,760
Visible that on lamp there's some drop, 218 V.

21
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:45,100
Output voltage went away from feedback trigger point and converter works in usual mode.

22
00:01:45,740 --> 00:01:46,920
No sound at all.

23
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:56,420
With voltage feedback present can supply at input voltage also higher.

24
00:01:57,240 --> 00:02:00,920
Inclusive 20 V higher not worth.

25
00:02:01,820 --> 00:02:04,420
Now supplied 14 V.

26
00:02:06,020 --> 00:02:15,020
Visible that voltage is within norm and feedback trigger sound appeared.

27
00:02:15,460 --> 00:02:24,260
Sound goes from step-up transformer, since microchip now controls keys in pulse bursts mode.

28
00:02:27,930 --> 00:02:31,850
If reduce, then sound disappears.

29
00:02:31,950 --> 00:02:33,910
Feedback fully works.

30
00:02:34,350 --> 00:02:37,930
To question what can connect to such converter.

31
00:02:39,130 --> 00:02:51,130
To it can connect all modern devices that have voltage inverter without transformer at input.

32
00:02:51,250 --> 00:03:00,230
That is, these are mobile phone chargers, laptop chargers, such devices.

33
00:03:00,570 --> 00:03:07,470
Can't connect device that contains step-down transformer at input.

34
00:03:07,930 --> 00:03:17,550
Such power supplies, their weight significantly higher than of inverter power supply.

35
00:03:17,970 --> 00:03:22,210
Also can't connect here asynchronous motors.

36
00:03:22,570 --> 00:03:27,770
Most often in everyday life we can meet them in fans, for example.

37
00:03:29,010 --> 00:03:34,790
And brush collector motors that are here, will work freely.

38
00:03:34,790 --> 00:03:46,390
That is various kind small drills at 220 volts, power up to 200 watts, this system will freely power.

39
00:03:47,570 --> 00:03:56,150
To supplement our scheme with voltage feedback, use property of microchip IR2153.

40
00:03:56,950 --> 00:04:06,630
If at third pin of this microchip apply logical zero, microchip stops generation on both channels.

41
00:04:07,470 --> 00:04:17,550
For this I stopped at variant with galvanic isolation OPTOCOUPLER, widespread PC817.

42
00:04:19,850 --> 00:04:26,390
Soldered it in this scheme, according to its leads.

43
00:04:27,110 --> 00:04:33,910
Leads 1 and 2 are infrared diode, built into OPTOCOUPLER.

44
00:04:34,730 --> 00:04:38,690
Third and fourth lead are opto-transistor.

45
00:04:39,770 --> 00:04:49,370
OPTOCOUPLER is such small detail, here it is, with four leads.

46
00:04:50,770 --> 00:05:01,430
On upper part of case there's dot, it means lead numbering.

47
00:05:01,550 --> 00:05:02,390
This is first lead.

48
00:05:02,870 --> 00:05:11,610
Leads, if observe from dot, in this case it's now located upper left corner, counted counter-clockwise.

49
00:05:11,730 --> 00:05:14,870
That is first, second, third and fourth.

50
00:05:15,530 --> 00:05:21,930
On scheme OPTOCOUPLER presented lying legs up.

51
00:05:22,930 --> 00:05:26,110
Like this now corresponds to its leads.

52
00:05:26,950 --> 00:05:30,270
So, solder OPTOCOUPLER into scheme.

53
00:05:31,530 --> 00:05:35,090
Here visible, I installed it on board.

54
00:05:35,430 --> 00:05:38,470
And check, does OPTOCOUPLER work.

55
00:05:39,390 --> 00:05:50,070
For this apply power to converter, preliminarily soldering small load to it.

56
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:54,230
In this case lamp 15 watts.

57
00:05:55,470 --> 00:05:57,430
Apply power.

58
00:06:00,310 --> 00:06:03,150
See, lamp lit.

59
00:06:03,970 --> 00:06:11,430
Now we need to solder to second lead of OPTOCOUPLER a wire.

60
00:06:12,050 --> 00:06:12,210
Here it is.

61
00:06:13,230 --> 00:06:19,050
And to first lead of OPTOCOUPLER current-limiting resistor 91 Ohm.

62
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:21,710
And one-and-half-volt battery.

63
00:06:22,630 --> 00:06:26,130
Minus from battery we supply to second leg.

64
00:06:26,790 --> 00:06:28,690
Plus to resistor.

65
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:31,990
And observe, I connect battery.

66
00:06:35,070 --> 00:06:44,830
And at connecting battery plus to resistor, microchip stops generation, load goes out.

67
00:06:46,970 --> 00:06:52,970
This experiment shows that OPTOCOUPLER is in working state.

68
00:06:53,790 --> 00:07:10,930
If there's lab signal generator on hand, can look how converter triggers under OPTOCOUPLER control with rectangular signal applied to input, common signal generator

69
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:18,690
connects to second lead, signal one to first lead, also through current-limiting resistance.

70
00:07:20,590 --> 00:07:24,150
Input potential supply not more than 5 V.

71
00:07:24,330 --> 00:07:29,810
Enough for OPTOCOUPLER triggering 1.5-2 V freely.

72
00:07:30,130 --> 00:07:32,510
Equivalent to what we did from battery.

73
00:07:32,770 --> 00:07:38,250
I supply rectangular signal with frequency 10 Hz.

74
00:07:39,310 --> 00:07:44,710
See that scheme excellently responds.

75
00:07:45,270 --> 00:07:46,510
Reduce frequency.

76
00:07:47,650 --> 00:07:49,030
Frequency 5 Hz.

77
00:07:50,130 --> 00:08:02,850
That is, understand, who deals with electronics, can on such principle already form microchip work in form of bursts.

78
00:08:05,390 --> 00:08:06,710
Frequency 1 Hz.

79
00:08:09,410 --> 00:08:16,750
If apply, say, mains frequency, here I smoothly raise, now 25 Hz.

80
00:08:21,390 --> 00:08:22,350
50.

81
00:08:22,610 --> 00:08:32,430
Can hear when will be such possibility to supply, that this step-up transformer hums at mains frequency 50 Hz.

82
00:08:33,690 --> 00:08:38,270
Further we need to introduce into scheme one more element.

83
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:41,050
This is microchip TL431.

84
00:08:42,390 --> 00:08:44,810
Graphically it presented as zener.

85
00:08:44,970 --> 00:08:49,210
With branch turns out controllable zener system.

86
00:08:50,310 --> 00:08:54,390
Pinout of leads presented under graphic image.

87
00:08:55,130 --> 00:08:59,370
Detail itself also very small.

88
00:08:59,890 --> 00:09:00,330
Here it is.

89
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:03,510
Three leads at detail.

90
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:13,870
Left to right counted leads, if microchip name reads directly frontally.

91
00:09:15,350 --> 00:09:16,810
What is this done for?

92
00:09:17,830 --> 00:09:36,570
Earlier I gave scheme of one more converter, and we can observe that here by feedback converter, master microchip, controlled directly through OPTOCOUPLER PC817 by means of dividing

93
00:09:36,570 --> 00:09:43,230
voltage on bundle of resistances connected in series.

94
00:09:44,050 --> 00:10:03,650
Here in this scheme can't control so, because if LED glow will be different intensity, accordingly and opto-transistor will, since it's bipolar, it will

95
00:09:36,570 --> 00:10:07,590
open with various degree of conductivity.

96
00:10:08,490 --> 00:10:15,810
And therefore, if measure it, play with OPTOCOUPLER, can see that resistance of this transistor changes.

97
00:10:16,350 --> 00:10:28,610
And for this microchip need order not less than 200 Ohm of resistance, to reliably short third leg to common wire.

98
00:10:29,330 --> 00:10:39,610
Precisely for this introduced additional sensitive element TL431 that controls this optocoupler.

99
00:10:40,590 --> 00:10:46,450
TL431 quite for us elderly microchip.

100
00:10:47,410 --> 00:10:55,210
Made it end 1970s, but nevertheless widely used till now.

101
00:10:56,390 --> 00:11:08,930
Its advantage is operating voltage up to 36 Volts and main possibility to set trigger points of this microchip.

102
00:11:09,850 --> 00:11:19,650
Inside there's reference power source about 2.5 Volts and comparator.

103
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:32,010
At one comparator input supplied stabilized power 2.5 Volts, and at other input supplied voltage from external part, from first lead.

104
00:11:32,530 --> 00:11:36,650
At that comparator compares reference and input voltage.

105
00:11:36,710 --> 00:11:48,570
If input voltage exceeds reference, microchip triggers and, graphically speaking, zener for us breaks down, that is microchip starts conducting.

106
00:11:49,450 --> 00:11:52,830
Picked I divider on resistors.

107
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:58,090
Resistors one-watt 4.6 kOhm and 390 kOhm.

108
00:11:58,530 --> 00:12:15,870
At such resistance, if its leads take already from converter output, voltage protection triggering happens at 238 Volts.

109
00:12:17,110 --> 00:12:27,690
That is, changing ratings of this resistance 4.6 kOhm, can set trigger point of converter.

110
00:12:28,690 --> 00:12:37,570
Mandatory need not forget to put this capacitor not less than 10 nF, ceramic, between third and first lead.

111
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:46,190
Otherwise possible false feedback triggers at some transient processes in transformer.

112
00:12:46,270 --> 00:12:54,950
For example, if there'll be needle-like voltage spikes, microchip will trigger earlier than needed.

113
00:12:55,230 --> 00:12:56,690
Capacitor mandatory.

114
00:12:57,830 --> 00:13:06,030
And this resistance that placed parallel to LED of optocoupler 1 kOhm.

115
00:13:06,610 --> 00:13:21,510
This resistance also doesn't let LED glow when microchip TL431 approaches trigger point.

116
00:13:22,790 --> 00:13:26,250
Limiting resistance 150 Ohm.

117
00:13:27,410 --> 00:13:34,570
Searched at start feedbacks of such kind in internet, but interesting, nothing found.

118
00:13:34,710 --> 00:13:42,670
Very many such solutions for low voltage, but with high voltage had to fiddle.

119
00:13:45,690 --> 00:13:54,810
Divider long picked in practice and changed various scheme variants, until it started working stably.

120
00:13:56,650 --> 00:14:10,250
Many details for this converter can be borrowed in some broken power supplies, for example, from computer power supplies.

121
00:14:11,930 --> 00:14:18,990
Can buy them cheaply or you may be given them at service centers just so.

122
00:14:20,570 --> 00:14:29,950
In particular can see that on board located optocoupler PC817 and this microchip.

123
00:14:32,270 --> 00:14:34,650
Small TL431.

124
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:40,850
Also heat sinks on which can plant transistors.

125
00:14:43,270 --> 00:14:48,270
Thermal insulation gaskets under these transistors, all can find here.

126
00:14:50,210 --> 00:14:53,010
Well and such also quite suits.

127
00:14:54,130 --> 00:14:57,150
Can it, this transformer disassemble.

128
00:14:58,430 --> 00:15:17,290
Soldered out it from board, but usually either heat it with construction dryer help until this glue melts so halves separate, or boil in water, also until it falls apart.

129
00:15:17,410 --> 00:15:26,290
After this all unwound, well and wound own winding according to desired voltages.

130
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:33,850
So this converter can come out very cheap if make it from recycled material.

131
00:15:36,450 --> 00:15:55,250
If this converter will be used, for example, for lighting when electric power supply turned off, then advise in this case put here at input some diode of any brand,

132
00:15:55,450 --> 00:15:58,430
no difference what find, at 20 A here.

133
00:15:59,210 --> 00:16:02,450
Voltage so order not less than 100 V.

134
00:16:04,770 --> 00:16:12,530
So in case of insufficient lighting not mix up these power inputs.

135
00:16:12,670 --> 00:16:23,430
Otherwise if mix up, scheme of course will immediately come into uselessness, microchip will fail and possibly one of keys will fly out.

136
00:16:24,810 --> 00:16:30,550
If it's connected stationary constantly, can not put diode.

137
00:16:31,470 --> 00:16:37,430
But also whoever wants can equip scheme input with fuse.

138
00:16:40,010 --> 00:16:43,530
That is at your discretion can upgrade this scheme.

139
00:16:43,530 --> 00:16:49,610
Also on such principle, this feedback I applied by voltage.

140
00:16:49,870 --> 00:17:04,210
I need operating voltage point so it'd be... If voltage feedback assembled, here can already at input supply not only 12 V but voltage up to 20 V inclusive, with this it'll

141
00:17:04,210 --> 00:17:07,030
stably hold output voltage.

142
00:17:07,150 --> 00:17:14,910
That is can even take in pocket two Krona-type batteries, connect them in series and supply at input 18 V.

143
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:20,570
And you'll have at output voltage 220 V.

144
00:17:20,570 --> 00:17:23,510
Always charge mobile phone.

145
00:17:26,870 --> 00:17:29,190
In whole scheme such flexible.

146
00:17:31,490 --> 00:17:37,110
Whoever interested can also assemble here current feedback.

147
00:17:37,190 --> 00:17:43,730
That is if interested specifically that at output shorting microchip went to protection.

148
00:17:43,830 --> 00:17:58,730
For this will need to change divider resistance, wind small toroidal transformer, so-called current transformer.

149
00:17:58,810 --> 00:18:09,390
Can hang it at this common point by power plus to middle point of primary winding.

150
00:18:10,070 --> 00:18:22,630
And already playing with its turn count, bring operating voltage point say somewhere above 2.6 V.

151
00:18:23,010 --> 00:18:30,310
Say if this converter works on load 200 V.

152
00:18:31,130 --> 00:18:40,090
And feed this output from this current sensor to small diode bridge.

153
00:18:40,430 --> 00:18:42,090
After this put capacity.

154
00:18:43,230 --> 00:18:49,190
Approximately scheme for you will turn out analog of this one presented.

155
00:18:49,230 --> 00:19:06,950
Diode bridge, capacity and already for you may turn out quite working system that'll protect converter from short voltage, that is from short circuit at its output.

156
00:19:08,420 --> 00:19:12,070
Everyone successful experiments, all good!
